\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {Madeleine rushed down the stone corridors of the Alchemy Faculty building, the sound of her boots echoing off the walls as she hurried toward her Herbology lab. Her satchel bounced against her side with each step, and she barely spared a glance at the enchanted timepiece hanging from her belt, the hands rapidly ticking past the minutes. She had completely lost track of time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 Damn it, Madeleine,}{ she thought, }{\f0\fs24\i1 how did I let this happen?}
\par\plain {She hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t meant to lose track of time. But between her backlog of Herbology assignments and the scrawled notes she\u8217\'92d been poring over\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 notes about the tiger, about Eddie, about that eerie resemblance\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it had all started to unravel. Something about it gnawed at her, a puzzle missing its center.}
\par\plain {She turned sharply down a narrow hallway, nearly colliding with a floating cart of flasks.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 Focus.}{\line }{\f0\fs24\i1 One thing at a time.}
\par\plain {The heavy oaken door to the Herbology lab loomed ahead, carved with ivy and curling vines that shimmered faintly in the light. As she reached for the handle, her heart pounded\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 half from the run, half from the fear that she was already too late.}
\par\plain {But the soft murmur of voices inside met her ears, and when she eased the door open, she exhaled with relief.}
\par\plain {The professor wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t here yet.}
\par\plain {Inside, students clustered in groups, tending to glass terrariums, adjusting runic lighting, or arguing softly over pruning techniques. The scent of damp moss and pollen clung to the air like mist.}
\par\plain {Madeleine slipped inside quietly, closing the heavy door behind her with a soft click. She scanned the room quickly, eyes darting over the clusters of students and their green, glowing plants, until they settled on a familiar figure near the back. Walther sat hunched over his workstation, his fingers moving steadily across a piece of parchment covered in neat, looping script.}
\par\plain {Without hesitation, Madeleine crossed the room and slid into the chair beside him. The moment her weight settled, the door creaked again\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Professor\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s arrival\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and the low hum of anticipation rippled through the lab.}
\par\plain {Walther looked up briefly, his dark eyes narrowing as he took in the flushed, breathless expression on her face. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Madeleine, you\u8217\'92re late,\u8221\'94 he said, voice quiet but edged with mild amusement. \u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re usually the first one here. What kept you? Another marathon at the Sanctuary?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {She swallowed, forcing a tired smile. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Something like that.\u8221\'94\line She didn\u8217\'92t want to say more, especially not here\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 not with half the class listening and Walther\u8217\'92s perceptive gaze pressing gently but firmly.\line Instead, she nodded toward his parchment. \u8220\'93What are you working on?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Walther\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s lips twitched into a rare, almost-smile. \u8220\'93Just some notes on the growth patterns of the Shadeleaf vine. It\u8217\'92s been acting\u8230\'85 unusual lately. I thought you\u8217\'92d want to know.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes flickered to the vine creeping near their workstation, its dark leaves twisting strangely toward the light. \u8220\'93Unusual how?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {He shrugged, but there was a tension beneath the movement. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hard to say. I\u8217\'92ll show you later. For now, just keep an eye on it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {She nodded again, grateful for the shift in focus. Here, at least, was a small fragment of normality.}
\par\plain {The professor\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s voice cut through the murmurs, drawing everyone\u8217\'92s attention. \u8220\'93Today, we will be testing hypotheses on the growth behaviors of }{\f0\fs24\i1 Luminara nox}{, a plant known for its bioluminescent properties in low-light environments. Your assignment is to observe and record the plant\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s response to varied light frequencies. You may begin.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Madeleine nodded absently, still feeling the weight of sleepless nights and the gnawing mystery at the back of her mind. She reached down to her satchel to pull out her binders, intending to get her notes ready.}
\par\plain {But as she yanked the bag up hastily, her tired fingers slipped. Instead of the binder\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s sturdy spine, her grip caught the loose papers tucked behind it. In an instant, a flurry of parchment spiraled out, fluttering down like autumn leaves across the stone floor.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, no,\u8221\'94 Madeleine muttered under her breath, cheeks flushing as she crouched to gather the scattered sheets.}
\par\plain {Walther, sitting beside her, was already reaching down to help, his calm presence a quiet anchor amid her embarrassment. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Here,\u8221\'94 he said softly, handing her a few papers with an easy efficiency.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thanks,\u8221\'94 she murmured, biting her lip as she carefully stacked them back into the binder.}
\par\plain {Madeleine crouched, carefully gathering the scattered papers with Walther\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s steady help. Each sheet slipped back into her binder brought a small wave of relief. Almost all of it was accounted for\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 except one.}
\par\plain {Her eyes followed Walther\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s gaze as he held a single page between his fingers. His expression shifted sharply, a flicker of something like horror mixed with disbelief crossing his usually unreadable face.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Walther?\u8221\'94 Madeleine\u8217\'92s voice was low but urgent. \u8220\'93Can you give me that?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {He didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t say a word, his fingers tightening around the paper as if it burned him. Her heart quickened, unease prickling beneath her skin.}
\par\plain {With a quick tug, she yanked the page from his grasp, pulling it closer to her. Her breath caught as she recognized the sketch sprawled across the parchment.}
\par\plain {It was the drawing she\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d made\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the detailed, haunting sketch Eddie had described to her of the tiger-human chimaera.}
\par\plain {Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s pulse hammered in her ears as Walther\u8217\'92s wide eyes met hers, his usual calm shattered for a fleeting moment. She quickly hid the paper beneath her binder, forcing her voice steady.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Where did you...?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Walther\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s lips pressed into a thin line, eyes darkening. For the first time, the mysterious distance around him felt like something more\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 something dangerous.}
\par\plain {Madeleine swallowed, her secret suddenly feeling heavier than ever. }
