\par\plain {The moon hung low over Edenfield\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s towering spires, its silver glow pooling on the cobbled pathways. Lanterns flickered in the cold breeze as Madeleine stepped out of the Alchemy building, tugging her scarf tighter and buttoning her coat all the way up to her chin. The night bit at her cheeks, and the long day pressed against her shoulders like a weight.}
\par\plain {She was halfway down the steps when she heard it.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Madeleine.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {She turned, catching sight of Walther\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s figure leaning against one of the columns, his silhouette long and still under the lanternlight.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, hey,\u8221\'94 she said, flashing her usual warm smile despite the late hour and her exhaustion. \u8220\'93What\u8217\'92s up?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Walther stepped closer. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I wanted to ask you something,\u8221\'94 he said, his voice quieter than usual, but no less firm. \u8220\'93That sketch you dropped earlier\u8230\'85 where did you get the idea for it?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Madeleine hesitated for a breath too long. Her mind spun.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Just... something I threw together,\u8221\'94 she said lightly, tucking her hands into her coat pockets. \u8220\'93A badly drawn South Alamirian Tiger, honestly. It\u8217\'92s not exactly accurate.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Walther didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t laugh. He didn\u8217\'92t even blink.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re lying,\u8221\'94 he said calmly. \u8220\'93Is this about Eddie? You think a South Alamirian Tiger attacked him?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {She glanced away, toward the line of trees swaying in the wind. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s just a hunch,\u8221\'94 she admitted, careful with her words.}
\par\plain {Walther stepped forward again, his brows lowering. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Madeleine, South Alamirian Tigers come from the eastern dunes. There hasn\u8217\'92t been one seen this far west in decades. Certainly not in Edenfield.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Madeleine met his gaze. Her voice was quiet, but steady. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know. That\u8217\'92s why I\u8217\'92m curious.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {A long pause hung between them, the cold wind threading between their words. Walther studied her with that same unreadable expression he always wore, but this time, something in his eyes looked sharper\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 cutting through the calm.}
\par\plain {And yet, he said nothing more. }
