\par\plain {The bus hissed to a stop at the edge of Aetherell Reach. Madeleine didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t wait for the doors to fully open before stepping down. She didn\u8217\'92t thank the driver\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a small, almost sacred courtesy she }{\f0\fs24\i1 never}{ forgot. But tonight, it slipped her completely.}
\par\plain {Her boots hit the pavement. Cold air bit at her cheeks.}
\par\plain {She moved fast.}
\par\plain {Only one thought screamed in her mind now: }{\f0\fs24\i1 Call Claire.}
\par\plain {If anyone could pull the others together on short notice, it was Claire\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 sharp, dependable Claire, who spent more time in the Edenfield Grand Library than most librarians. She would know how to reach Will, Ashley\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85 and Eddie.}
\par\plain {Madeleine spotted the phone booth at the corner just beyond the wrought-iron fence, tucked beneath a flickering lantern. She broke into a brisk jog, her satchel thudding against her side.}
\par\plain {Fumbling the door open, she stepped inside, heart thumping in her throat. The glass was fogged from the cold, her breath blooming across the surface as she picked up the receiver with slightly trembling fingers.}
\par\plain {She slipped a coin into the slot.}
\par\plain {Dialled the number from memory.}
\par\plain {The ring buzzed against her ear. Once. Twice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 C\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92mon, Claire. Please pick up.}
\par\plain {Each second stretched taut, a string pulled tighter and tighter. Madeleine glanced over her shoulder through the fogged glass, as if expecting someone\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 or something\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to be there.}
\par\plain {The phone clicked.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hello?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Madeleine exhaled in relief. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Claire. It\u8217\'92s me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Madeleine? Is everything alright? You sound\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Listen,\u8221\'94 she cut in, her voice low, urgent. \u8220\'93I need your help. I need everyone gathered at the library. Will, Ashley, Eddie. As soon as possible. Tonight.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {There was a pause.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Tonight?\u8221\'94 Claire echoed, clearly startled. \u8220\'93What\u8217\'92s going on?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it\u8217\'92s Walther, I think he\u8217\'92s\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 Bzzzt.}
\par\plain {A loud burst of static drowned her out. The line went dead.}
\par\plain {Madeleine blinked. Pulled the receiver away from her ear. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Claire?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {She wrenched it back, hit the switch to redial, heart slamming in her chest.}
\par\plain {Nothing. Just a hollow whirring. Then more static.}
\par\plain {She slammed her fist against the side of the booth in frustration, breath fogging the glass. }{\f0\fs24\i1 Come on, come on\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 }
\par\plain {She checked over her shoulder again.}
\par\plain {That\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s when she saw it.}
\par\plain {A silhouette.}
\par\plain {Tall. Motionless. Just past the edge of the gaslamp's glow. Unmoving, yet undeniably there, cloaked in darkness.}
\par\plain {Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart dropped. Her breath hitched.}
\par\plain {She spun back to the phone, redialled furiously. Her fingers shook. }{\f0\fs24\i1 One more time. Just one more time\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 }
\par\plain {The silhouette stepped closer.}
\par\plain {Now within the haze of the lamp\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s flickering light. Its outline was still indistinct, the shadows swallowing every feature\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 but it was }{\f0\fs24\i1 walking toward her.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Pick up\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 pick up\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {A soft }{\f0\fs24\i1 click.}{ Then: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hello?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Claire!\u8221\'94 Madeleine gasped. \u8220\'93I\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 I think someone\u8217\'92s\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {She turned slowly, hand tightening on the receiver cord.}
\par\plain {The figure was now just under the gaslamp. The light illuminated its feet. Then its hands.}
\par\plain {Gloved.}
\par\plain {Still, no face.}
\par\plain {Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s breath turned shallow, her instincts screaming.}
\par\plain {Her hand dove into her satchel, fingers fumbling past parchment and bottles until they closed around the smooth wood of her wand.}
\par\plain {She drew it in a single motion and pointed it straight toward the shadow.}
\par\plain {But it was too late.}
\par\plain {The booth\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s light burst above her\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 }{\f0\fs24\i1 pop}{\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and the world plunged into darkness.}}